Package ConcreteDomain.AtomicTypes

Class ConstantObject

  • java.lang.Object
    • ConcreteDomain.ConcreteObject
      • ConcreteDomain.AtomicObject
        • ConcreteDomain.AtomicTypes.ConstantObject
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    DataObject, java.io.Serializable

    public class ConstantObject
extends AtomicObject
implements java.io.Serializable
    This class is just a wrapper for strings. If two Constants are parsed with parseString then two strings which are equal become identical objects. Therefore they can be compared with ==.
    Example: Nationalities: German, French, Italian etc.
    See Also:
